            <title>[TIKA-4350] HTML snippet containing &lt;iframe&gt; as root element erroneously recognized as application/xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-4350</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A HTML snippet containing an &amp;lt;iframe&amp;gt; element as document root is erroneously recognized as &lt;tt&gt;application/xml&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was reported on the Nutch user mailing list for Nutch 1.19 using Tika 2.3.0:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread/fhhp1p6y4ttxmplvz1ohk3wwjz25ozbc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread/fhhp1p6y4ttxmplvz1ohk3wwjz25ozbc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is reproducible with Tika 3.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
